Package: foster
Type: Package
Title: FOrest Structure Extrapolation with R
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
  person("Martin","Queinnec",email="martin.queinnec@gmail.com",role=c("cre","aut")))
Maintainer: Martin Queinnec <martin.queinnec@gmail.com>
Description: This package contains function that can be used to extrapolate sparse 
  forest attribute data on larger scale using a k-NN imputation approach. FOSTER allows to perform the following tasks: 
  data preprocessing (Resampling, cropping, masking, smoothing raster datasets), 
  calculating spectral indices and summarize time-series of variables to be used as predictors, 
  selecting training and testing samples using a stratified random selection approach,
  training a k-NN model and assess its accuracy, 
  imputing response variables simultaneously on a large scale using the trained k-NN model. 
